%N A099218 Decimal expansion of Li_4(1/2).
%D A099218 Alexander Apelblat, Tables of Integrals and Series, Harri Deutsch, (1996), Section 1.3.2.
%H A099218 George Rutledge and R. D. Douglass, <a href="https://doi.org/10.2307/2303745">Table of definite integrals</a>, Am. Math. Monthly 45 (8) (1938), 525-530, eq. (22).
%H A099218 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-030-02462-8">(Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer International Publishing, 2019, section 4.49, pp. 306-307, section 5.49, p. 326, section 6.49, pp. 490-495.
%F A099218 Equals Sum_{k>0} 1/(2^k*k^4).
%F A099218 From _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 25 2026: (Start)
%F A099218 Equals (1/12) * Intergral_{x>=0} x^3/(exp(x)-1/2) dx.
%F A099218 Equals (-1/2) * Intergral_{x=0..1} log(x)^2*log(1-x/2)/x dx. (End)
%F A099218 Equals Sum_{k>=1} H(k,3)/(k*2^(k+1)) + Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * (H(k)^3/12 + H(k,3)/6 + H(k)*H(k,2)/4)/(k*(k + 1)), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2, and H(k,3) = A007408(k)/A007409(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 3 (Vălean, 2019). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 16 2026
